2 Variable

Run the input coding, then out the output information.

# input coding
## [1] "That is the output."

2.1 Types

2.1.1 integer

Let \(x=2\), that’s the same effect down below.

x <- 2
x = 2
x
## [1] 2

2.1.2 character

Let \(x="words"\).

x = "words"
x
## [1] "words"

2.1.3 function

Like a machine, we got input, then we got output.

  • print(), print is a function for showing the data in variable.
x = 2
print(x)
## [1] 2
  • construct a new function
f = function(x,y){
  return(x+y)
}

print(f(3,7))
## [1] 10

2.1.4 sequence

Let \(x = (1,2,3,4,5)\)

x = seq(from=1,to=5,by=1)
print(x)
## [1] 1 2 3 4 5

2.1.5 vector

Let \(x=(1,5,tokens,4,name)\)

x = c(1,5,'tokens',4,'name')
print(x)
## [1] "1"      "5"      "tokens" "4"      "name"

2.1.5 factor

Let \(x=(A,A,B,A,C)\)

x = factor(x=c('A','A','B','A','C'))
print(x)
## [1] A A B A C
## Levels: A B C

2.1.6 matrix

x = matrix(data = c(1,2,3,
                    4,5,6), ncol = 3, nrow = 2, byrow = T)
print(x)
##      [,1] [,2] [,3]
## [1,]    1    2    3
## [2,]    4    5    6

2.1.7 data frame

x = as.data.frame(matrix(data = c(1,2,3,
                    4,5,6), ncol = 3, nrow = 2, byrow = T))
rownames(x) = c('x1', 'x2')
print(x)
##    V1 V2 V3
## x1  1  2  3
## x2  4  5  6

2.1.8 list

a set or a collection of all kinds of data

list1 = list(int1 = 1,
             char1 = 'character',
             seq1 = seq(from=1,to=6,by=1),
             vec = c(1,5,'tokens',4,'name'),
             fac = factor(x=c('A','A','B','A','C')),
             matr = matrix(data = c(1,2,3,
                    4,5,6), ncol = 3, nrow = 2, byrow = T),
             data_frame = as.data.frame(matrix(data = c(1,2,3,
                                                        4,5,6), ncol = 3, nrow = 2, byrow = T)))

list1
## $int1
## [1] 1
## 
## $char1
## [1] "character"
## 
## $seq1
## [1] 1 2 3 4 5 6
## 
## $vec
## [1] "1"      "5"      "tokens" "4"      "name"  
## 
## $fac
## [1] A A B A C
## Levels: A B C
## 
## $matr
##      [,1] [,2] [,3]
## [1,]    1    2    3
## [2,]    4    5    6
## 
## $data_frame
##   V1 V2 V3
## 1  1  2  3
## 2  4  5  6
